//pizza Badami,Karnataka The Badami Cave Temples are a complex of Hindu, Jain, and Buddhist cave temples located in Badami, Karnataka, India. They were constructed during the rule of the Chalukya dynasty, between the 6th and 8th centuries AD. These rock-cut temples are renowned for their stunning architecture, intricate carvings, and religious significance, making them a UNESCO World Heritage site.
