Kumbakonam,Tamil nadu The Airavatesvara Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva and is located in Darasuram, near Kumbakonam, Tamil Nadu, India. It was built by the Chola dynasty in the 12th century AD. This temple is renowned for its exquisite architecture, intricate carvings, and rich sculptural details, making it a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The Airavatesvara Temple is considered one of the finest examples of Dravidian architecture and attracts visitors from around the world.
